 MBOMBELA – Pro-Life Pet Rescue, Rehabilitation and Adoption Agency founder, Karin Erasmus and her fiancé appeared in the Nelspruit District Court on a charge of  perjury today. They were arrested at the sanctuary on Wednesday and released on a warning. AlSO READ: Sudwala farmer burgled by suspected ex-workers According to police spokesman, Lt Col Erhard Stroh, the arrests stemmed from the alleged theft of a firearm from their shared home on June 30. According to Stroh, upon investigation police discovered that the firearm had not been in the safe, but was kept in a side drawer. The court matter was postponed until August 2, pending further investigation. An extensive account of the incident will appear in the printed editon of Lowvelder of Friday, July 13.